```holoscript
object Ball @grabbable {
  geometry: 'sphere'
  physics: { mass: 0.5 }
}
```

The `@grabbable` trait enables picking up objects in VR. Physics is required for grabbable objects.

```holoscript
object ThrowableCube @grabbable @throwable {
  geometry: 'cube'
  physics: {
    mass: 0.5
    restitution: 0.6
  }
}
```

Combine `@grabbable` with `@throwable` for throwing. The `restitution` property controls bounciness (0-1).

```holoscript
object Button @pointable {
  geometry: 'cylinder'
  scale: [0.1, 0.02, 0.1]
  color: 'red'

  onPoint: {
    audio.play('click')
  }
}
```

The `@pointable` trait makes objects respond to VR pointer/gaze. Use `onPoint:` for click handlers.

```holoscript
object HighlightCube @hoverable {
  geometry: 'cube'
  color: '#4488cc'

  onHoverEnter: {
    this.color = '#66aaff'
    this.scale = 1.1
  }

  onHoverExit: {
    this.color = '#4488cc'
    this.scale = 1.0
  }
}
```

The `@hoverable` trait adds hover detection. Use `onHoverEnter` and `onHoverExit` for visual feedback.

```holoscript
object Glass @grabbable @throwable @breakable {
  geometry: 'model/glass.glb'
  physics: { mass: 0.3 }

  breakable: {
    threshold: 3
    shatterPattern: 'glass'
  }
}
```

The `@breakable` trait makes objects destructible. Set `threshold` for break force and `shatterPattern` for visual effect.

```holoscript
object SharedBall @grabbable @networked {
  geometry: 'sphere'

  @networked position
  @networked rotation
  @networked owner: null

  onGrab(player): {
    if (network.requestOwnership(this)) {
      this.owner = player.id
    }
  }
}
```

The `@networked` trait syncs object state across multiplayer sessions. Mark which properties to sync.

